ocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529672\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529672\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 25, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lqh1665702758875.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lqh1665702758875.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lqh1665702758875.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lqh1665702758875\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"lqh1665702758875__sax_callback_operations_445833\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">SAX callback operations are APIs that can be implemented on a user-defined SAX event handler. They enable you to use the parser information to manipulate and analyze XML data, and handle any errors that may be encountered.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lqh1665702758875__p_d136778e1_d136779e1_d136780e1\">SAX stands for Simple API for XML. It is a standard for accessing information in XML documents using a programming language and a parser for that language. Originally for Java only, there are now versions for several programming language environments.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lqh1665702758875__p_d136781e1_d136782e1_d136783e1\">XML namespaces are supported (on Windows, Unix and Linux), either by using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">STARTPREFIXMAPPING</span> or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ENDPREFIXMAPPING</span> operations in your SAX event handler, or by implementing the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">STARTELEMENT</span> or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ENDELEMENT</span> operations with namespace-specific parameters.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lqh1665702758875__topic_d97457e1_d97458e1_d97459e1_d97460e1_d97461e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d370257e70\">Operations</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lqh1665702758875__p_d136787e1_d136788e1_d136789e1\">For\n            descriptions of the available operations, see the related topics.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lqh1665702758875__p_d136790e1_d136791e1_d136792e1\">The SAX parser included with Uniface supports the following callback operations:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Supported SAX Callback Operations</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n Operation\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"myh1665702758943.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/myh1665702758943.html\" title=\"Generates the beginning of the document, optionally with the XML version header.\">STARTDOCUMENT</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\">Activated when the parser starts reading the\n                        document. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kpe1665702759011.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kpe1665702759011.html\" title=\"End the XML document, closing all open tags.\">ENDDOCUMENT</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\">Activated when the end of the document is\n                        reached. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rcp1665702759080.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rcp1665702759080.html\" title=\"Operation activated by the SAX parser when it encounters a start tag with one or more xmlns (namespace) specifications.\">STARTPREFIXMAPPING</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\">Activated when the parser encounters a\n                        namespace (<code class=\"ph codeph\">xmlns</code> ) specification in a start tag.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xzo1665702759148.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xzo1665702759148.html\" title=\"Operation activated by the SAX parser for each namespace specification in a start tag, when the parser encounters the corresponding end tag.\">ENDPREFIXMAPPING</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\">Activated for each namespace specification when\n                        the parser encounters the end tag for a start tag that holds a namespace\n                        specification.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yvg1665702759219.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yvg1665702759219.html\" title=\"Starts a new element using the name, including optional prefix and URI elements.\">STARTELEMENT</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\">Activated when the parser encounters a start\n                        tag, for example <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;tagA&gt;</code>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mdp1665702759283.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mdp1665702759283.html\" title=\"Ends an XML element by adding the closing tag.\">ENDELEMENT</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\">Activated when the parser encounters an end tag\n                        such as <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;/tagA&gt;</code>. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bry1665702759353.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bry1665702759353.html\" title=\"Adds the supplied text inside an element.\">CHARACTERS</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\">Activated when character data is encountered\n                        between a tag and its end tag.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xhr1665702759421.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xhr1665702759421.html\" title=\"Operation called by the SAX parser when it encounters a comment in the XML document.\">COMMENT</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\"> Activated when an XML comment is encountered\n                           (<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;!-- --&gt;</code>).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cux1665702759488.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cux1665702759488.html\" title=\"Operation activated by the SAX parser when it encounters character data that it considers to be ignorable whitespace.\">WHITESPACE</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\">Activated when the parser encounters character\n                        data that it considers to be ignorable whitespace.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jiy1665702759561.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jiy1665702759561.html\" title=\"Operation activated by the SAX parser when it encounters a notation declaration in a DTD.\">NOTATIONDECL</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\">Activated when the parser encounters a notation\n                        declaration in a DTD.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ztp1665702759633.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ztp1665702759633.html\" title=\"Operation activated by the SAX parser when it encounters external DTD declarations and unrecognized XML entity references. It must return the text or DTD to be substituted at the reference location.\">RESOLVEENTITY</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\">Activated when the parser encounters external\n                        DTD declarations and unrecognized XML entity references.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zso1665702759701.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zso1665702759701.html\" title=\"Operation activated by the SAX parser when it encounters entity declarations in a DTD that contain the NDATA keyword.\">UNPARSEDENTITY</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\">Activated when the parser encounters entity\n                        declarations in a DTD that contain the NDATA keyword.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ene1665702759768.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ene1665702759768.html\" title=\"Operation activated by the SAX parser when a processing instruction is encountered.\">PROCESSINGINST</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\">Activated when the parser encounters a\n                        processing instruction.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gst1665702684426.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gst1665702684426.html\" title=\"Returns the Uniface message number for the error.\">$error</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\">Activated when the parser issues a recoverable\n                        error.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hnh1665702759840.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hnh1665702759840.html\" title=\"Operation activated by the SAX parser when it issues a non-recoverable error.\">FATALERROR</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\">Activated when the parser issues a\n                        non-recoverable error.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dhb1665702759914.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dhb1665702759914.html\" title=\"Operation called by the SAX parser when it issues a warning.\">WARNING</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"lqh1665702758875__table_d16310e1_d16311e1_d16312e1__entry__2\">Activated when the parser issues a\n                        warning.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xjf1665702758735.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Creating a SAX Event Handler</a><p>Before starting to parse XML documents using the UXMLREADER component, you need to implement the operations that handle parser events, such as starting and ending the document and elements, and error handling.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529672\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529672\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "SAX Callback Operations Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 25, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 SAX callback operations are APIs that can be implemented on a user-defined SAX event handler. They enable you to use the parser information to manipulate and analyze XML data, and handle any errors that may be encountered. SAX stands for Simple API for XML. It is a standard for accessing information in XML documents using a programming language and a parser for that language. Originally for Java only, there are now versions for several programming language environments. XML namespaces are supported (on Windows, Unix and Linux), either by using the STARTPREFIXMAPPING or ENDPREFIXMAPPING operations in your SAX event handler, or by implementing the STARTELEMENT or ENDELEMENT operations with namespace-specific parameters. Operations For descriptions of the available operations, see the related topics. The SAX parser included with Uniface supports the following callback operations: Table 1. Supported SAX Callback Operations Operation Description STARTDOCUMENT Activated when the parser starts reading the document. ENDDOCUMENT Activated when the end of the document is reached. STARTPREFIXMAPPING Activated when the parser encounters a namespace ( xmlns ) specification in a start tag. ENDPREFIXMAPPING Activated for each namespace specification when the parser encounters the end tag for a start tag that holds a namespace specification. STARTELEMENT Activated when the parser encounters a start tag, for example <tagA> . ENDELEMENT Activated when the parser encounters an end tag such as </tagA> . CHARACTERS Activated when character data is encountered between a tag and its end tag. COMMENT Activated when an XML comment is encountered ( <!-- --> ). WHITESPACE Activated when the parser encounters character data that it considers to be ignorable whitespace. NOTATIONDECL Activated when the parser encounters a notation declaration in a DTD. RESOLVEENTITY Activated when the parser encounters external DTD declarations and unrecognized XML entity references. UNPARSEDENTITY Activated when the parser encounters entity declarations in a DTD that contain the NDATA keyword. PROCESSINGINST Activated when the parser encounters a processing instruction. $error Activated when the parser issues a recoverable error. FATALERROR Activated when the parser issues a non-recoverable error. WARNING Activated when the parser issues a warning. Related Links Creating a SAX Event Handler Before starting to parse XML documents using the UXMLREADER component, you need to implement the operations that handle parser events, such as starting and ending the document and elements, and error handling. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}